        "timestamp": 1773623658
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>are you a roc expert ?</p>",
        "id": 579594851,
        "sender_full_name": "daniel",
        "timestamp": 1773623759
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>haha, idk about an expert... <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span>  -- I've been lurking around here for a long time though</p>",
        "id": 579594987,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1773623785
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but you have mod status ?</p>",
        "id": 579595362,
        "sender_full_name": "daniel",
        "timestamp": 1773623859
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am. I also contribute a fair amount to the core compiler and various platforms/packages.</p>",
        "id": 579595986,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1773623982
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there something your interested to know about?</p>",
        "id": 579596093,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1773624001
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ok more than just lurking</p>",
        "id": 579596127,
        "sender_full_name": "daniel",
        "timestamp": 1773624006
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the FAQ says there is a kind of effect system. but as i see there are  no monads</p>",
        "id": 579596359,
        "sender_full_name": "daniel",
        "timestamp": 1773624047
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Side effects are managed by the platform, not the application code. When you write an app you choose a platform (e.g. basic-cli, basic-webserver) and the platform is responsible for actually performing the I/O.</p>",
        "id": 579597754,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1773624358
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ok  the FAQ  is maybe not accurate anymore</p>",
        "id": 579597894,
        "sender_full_name": "daniel",
        "timestamp": 1773624445
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>would you mind pointing me to the FAQ spot so I can make an issue if its out of date</p>",
        "id": 579598110,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1773624590
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh not in FAQ. it is here : <a href=\"https://www.roc-lang.org/functional#managed-effects\">https://www.roc-lang.org/functional#managed-effects</a></p>",
        "id": 579598359,
        "sender_full_name": "daniel",
        "timestamp": 1773624805
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes I think that is out of date. Particularly in the new zig compiler (the re-write which is almost done) -- the concept of <strong>effectful</strong> functions using the <code>!</code> and <code>=&gt;</code> syntax.</p>",
        "id": 579598585,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1773624981
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is a more up to date reference <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/blob/main/docs/mini-tutorial-new-compiler.md#pure-and-effectful-function-types\">https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/blob/main/docs/mini-tutorial-new-compiler.md#pure-and-effectful-function-types</a></p>",
        "id": 579598724,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1773625061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Unfortunately -- we are in a spot right now where user friendly docs are being re-written so I don't have a lot to point at</p>",
        "id": 579598765,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1773625089
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ok thx</p>",
